    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="568"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d568">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 10170/3–4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mexican Chargé</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexican Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1908</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 127.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Most Excellent Sir</hi>: Referring to the extradition case
                    of George Deering Reed, I have the honor to inform you, as you will please see
                    from the record of proceedings in the case which I send you under separate
                    cover, together with the requisite certificate of Judge Lanning, of the District
                    Court of New Jersey, that a favorable decision has been already given in the
                    case and an order issued that the offender may be delivered to the Mexican
                    authorities.</p>
                <p>By virtue thereof, I beg that, in the absence of any objection, you may be
                    pleased to issue the requisite warrant for the surrender of the offender.</p>
                <p>Accept anew, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">José F. Godoy.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
